#Template: DigitalProspects/configuration/note
#Type: note
#Description: Package configuration note
# DigitalProspects can be and should be configured entirely via web, so, in the
# following configuration steps, I'm going to prompt you for the passwords that
# DigitalProspects uses for web configuration and some default values for the
# application startup. Then you should point your browser to the DigitalProspects
# setup, for example:
# .
# http://localhost/DigitalProspects/install.php
# .
# continue the configuration, fill the database and let DigitalProspects be aware of
# the installed modules.

#Template: DigitalProspects/webserver
#Type: select
#Choices: Apache, Apache-ssl, Both, None
#Description: Which Web Server are you running ?
# DigitalProspects supports any web server with PHP capabilities, but this
# configuration process only supports Apache and Apache-SSL.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db
#Type: text
#Description: DigitalProspects DB setup note
# Now you should specify the DBMS settings. You must provide the host name on
# which the DBMS server is installed, the type (i.e.  MySql), the DB name, the DBMS administrator user-name, etc.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/host
#Type: string
#Default: localhost
#Description: Please, insert your database host name:
# This should be the host-name or IP address that DigitalProspects will use to access
# the DB.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/port
#Type: string
#Default: 3306
#Description: Please, insert your database port:
# This should be the port value that DigitalProspects will use to access
# the DB.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/name
#Type: string
#Default: DigitalProspects
#Description: Please, insert DigitalProspects database name:
# This is the name of the database that DigitalProspects will use.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/user/name
#Type: string
#Default: DigitalProspects
#Description: Please, insert the DBMS user-name to access the DB:
# This is the user-name that DigitalProspects will use to access the DB.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/user/password
#Type: password
#Description: Please, insert the password to access the DB:
# This is the password that DigitalProspects will use, along with user-name you
# provided, to access the DB.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/user/password/confirm
#Type: password
#Description: Please, retype the password to access the DB:
# Please insert the DB access password again. If the password you are going to
# retype mismatch the previous inserted one, I'll ask you to insert them again.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/user/password/mismatch
#Type: text
#Description: Passwords mismatch
# The DB access passwords you inserted mismatch. Please, try again.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/admin/name
#Type: string
#Default: root
#Description: Please, insert the DBMS administrator user-name:
# This user-name will be used to access the DBMS to create (if needed):
# .
#  (1) The new DigitalProspects database
#  (2) The new database account that DigitalProspects will use to access the DB
# .
# It should be 'root' for MySql.

#Template: DigitalProspects/db/admin/password
#Type: password
#Description: Please, insert the DBMS administrator password (if any):
# This is the password that will be used along with the DBMS administrator
# user-name.
# .
# NOTE: This password will not be asked twice, since it's not a new password.

Template: DigitalProspects/postrm
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Delete database ?
 Delete the DigitalProspects MySQL database and all its datas (datas related
 to this quetion are the DigitalProspects DBMS account and all
 DigitalProspects tables) ?

#Template: DigitalProspects/postrmfile
#Type: boolean
#Default: true
#Description: Delete attached files ?
# Delete also all uploaded and generated files (datas related
# to this quetion are all files found into /usr/share/DigitalProspects/documents,
# uploaded or generated when using DigitalProspects) ?
 